        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(embedded-runner): expose prep stage timings",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Expose embedded runner prep stage snapshots on `EmbeddedRunAttemptResult`.\n- Include the same prep stage summary on the `agent_end` hook event for plugin observability.\n- Add focused coverage for attempt result and hook event prep stage propagation.\n- Document the new optional hook field. No `CHANGELOG.md` change is kept.\n\n## Current upstream status\nLatest `origin/main` already has May embedded-runner/subagent performance work and trace logging for startup stages. It still does not expose the attempt prep stage summary to `agent_end` hook observers. This PR is narrowed to that missing diagnostics surface so plugins can collect stage timing evidence without patching core locally.\n\n## Motivation\nOpenClaw records detailed embedded runner prep stages internally, but that timing data is not available to plugin hooks. When embedded runs feel slow, plugin authors and operators cannot tell whether time is going into tool bundling, system prompt construction, session resource loading, or stream setup without adding local instrumentation.\n\nExposing the existing stage snapshot gives downstream integrations a low-risk way to collect latency evidence before proposing behavior-changing optimizations.\n\n## Implementation notes\n- Reuses the existing `createEmbeddedRunStageTracker()` / `prepStages.snapshot()` path.\n- Keeps all new fields optional.\n- Uses public structural plugin hook types instead of exporting runner internals through the plugin API.\n- Does not change tool bundling, system prompt construction, stream setup, model calls, or runner behavior.\n- Documents `agent_end.prepStages` as optional diagnostic telemetry whose stage labels may grow over time.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Embedded runner prep stage timings are visible to a real non-bundled plugin's `agent_end` hook without changing the embedded run outcome.\n\nReal environment tested: macOS local OpenClaw source checkout, current PR head `8d7ef409272853778bd234da21e777ac880216a6`, temporary `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, temporary `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`, temporary local plugin loaded through `plugins.load.paths` with `hooks.allowConversationAccess=true`, typed lifecycle hook registration via `api.on(\"agent_end\", ...)`, `node scripts/run-node.mjs agent --local --json --session-key agent:default:prep-proof`, and the repo mock OpenAI-compatible server `scripts/e2e/mock-openai-server.mjs`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Started the mock OpenAI server with `SUCCESS_MARKER=OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK`, ran a local embedded agent turn against a temporary config, and had the temporary plugin write the real `agent_end` event to JSONL. The proof script asserted both the CLI result and plugin hook payload.\n\nFresh current-head verification:\n\n```text\nnode --max-old-space-size=8192 --import tsx scripts/generate-plugin-sdk-api-baseline.ts --check\nOK docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-embedded-agent.config.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-engine.test.ts -t \"exposes embedded prep stages\" --reporter=dot\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  1 passed | 58 skipped (59)\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: copied live terminal output from the current-head local OpenClaw CLI run and typed non-bundled plugin `agent_end` hook JSONL assertion.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"8d7ef409272853778bd234da21e777ac880216a6\",\n  \"finalAssistantVisibleText\": \"OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK\",\n  \"hookSuccess\": true,\n  \"hookHasPrepStages\": true,\n  \"hookTotalMs\": 143,\n  \"hookStageNames\": [\n    \"workspace-sandbox\",\n    \"skills\",\n    \"core-plugin-tools\",\n    \"bootstrap-context\",\n    \"bundle-tools\",\n    \"system-prompt\",\n    \"session-resource-loader\",\n    \"agent-session\",\n    \"stream-setup\"\n  ],\n  \"proofDir\": \"/tmp/openclaw-78381-proof-current.Xjp9Fj\"\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A standalone embedded `openclaw agent --local` run completed successfully against the mock OpenAI server, returned `OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK`, and the temporary plugin's real typed `agent_end` handler observed `event.prepStages` with total setup time and expected prep stages.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live paid external model/provider run was not run. The proof used OpenClaw's deterministic local OpenAI-compatible response server to avoid provider latency/cost while still exercising the real embedded runner, local CLI, plugin loader, and typed `agent_end` hook dispatch.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n- Backward compatible? `Yes`\n- Config/env changes? `No`\n- Migration needed? `No`\n- Risk: plugin authors might treat stage names as permanent.\n- Mitigation: docs describe `prepStages` as optional diagnostics and allow stage labels to grow over time.\n\n\n\n\n",
